name: LSD Depth Perception Tracers
description:
n.1 on Psychotropic Distortion Collection 
 
///////////////////////////////////////

Tracers are defined as the experience of trails of varying lengths and opacity being left behind moving objects in a manner that is similar to those found in long exposure photography. https://psychonautwiki.org/wiki/Tracers

Depth perception distortions are defined as alterations in how a person perceives the distance of various objects within their visual field. During this state, the various layers of scenery can become exaggerated, skewed, or completely rearranged. 
https://psychonautwiki.org/wiki/Depth_perception_distortions
